      "content": "The argument suggesting biological or cultural components often relies on selective interpretations of data that link specific group characteristics to higher crime rates. Proponents of this view point to observed statistical correlations as evidence of inherent differences within those populations. However, the vast majority of modern criminological and genetic science rejects the notion of inherent biological determinism for criminal behavior. These arguments are largely considered pseudoscientific by the mainstream academic community.",
